org.radarcns.oauth

Class OAuth2AccessTokenDetails

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.radarcns.oauth.OAuth2AccessTokenDetails

  • public class OAuth2AccessTokenDetails
extends java.lang.Object
    This class captures the response from ManagementPortal's /oauth/token endpoint. The actual access token can be retrieved with the getAccessToken() method. This is a token in JWT format, and can be parsed with a JWT library of your preference. You can ise isValid() to check if you got a valid token, or an error response. If isValid() returns false, you can use getError() and getErrorDescription() to find the error message that was returned by ManagementPortal. You can also use isExpired() to find out if the token has expired or not. However it is advised to use the OAuth2Client class, as it will automatically manage token refreshing and checking validity.
